"cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782351993039, "responseId": "resp_0b175672a34e51cb016a3c887998d481968861f2ef3d90145d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_EpppY0Flmuu4nBRiqsS6MHdr|fc_0b175672a34e51cb016a3c887d5ed481969cfaebac71b91fea", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "URL https://mockk.io/\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"MockK\" />\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" />\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Provides DSL to mock behavior. Built from zero to fit Kotlin language. Supports named parameters, object mocks, coroutines and extension function mocking\" />\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://mockk.io/\" />\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"MockK\" />\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"website\" />\n<meta property=\"twitter:title\" content=\"MockK\" />\n    <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://mockk.io/doc/stats-shared.png\"/>\n<p>All you need to get started is just to add a dependency to <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">MockK</code> library.</p>\n<h4 id=\"gradlemaven-dependency\">Gradle/Maven dependency</h4>\ntestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk:${mockkVersion}\"\n  <pre>testImplementation(\"io.mockk:mockk:${mockkVersion}\")</pre>\n &lt;dependency&gt;\n &lt;/dependency&gt;\ntestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-android:${mockkVersion}\"\ntestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-agent:${mockkVersion}\"\nandroidTestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-android:${mockkVersion}\"\nandroidTestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-agent:${mockkVersion}\"\n<div class=\"language-gradle highlighter-rouge\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre class=\"highlight\"><code><span class=\"n\">testImplementation</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"io.mockk:mockk:${mockkVersion}\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">testImplementation</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"io.mockk:mockk-bdd:${mockkVersion}\"</span>\n<div class=\"language-gradle highlighter-rouge\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre class=\"highlight\"><code><span class=\"n\">androidTestImplementation</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"io.mockk:mockk-android:${mockkVersion}\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">androidTestImplementation</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"io.mockk:mockk-bdd-android:${mockkVersion}\"</span>\n      <li><a href=\"#gradlemaven-dependency\" id=\"markdown-toc-gradlemaven-dependency\">Gradle/Maven dependency</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#injectmockks-dependency-order\" id=\"markdown-toc-injectmockks-dependency-order\">@InjectMockKs dependency order</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"#declarative-enabling-of-dependency-order\" id=\"markdown-toc-declarative-enabling-of-dependency-order\">Declarative enabling of dependency order</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#relaxed-mock\" id=\"markdown-toc-relaxed-mock\">Relaxed mock</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#mock-relaxed-for-functions-returning-unit\" id=\"markdown-toc-mock-relaxed-for-functions-returning-unit\">Mock relaxed for functions returning Unit</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#property-backing-fields\" id=\"markdown-toc-property-backing-fields\">Property backing fields</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://medium.com/joe-tsai/mockk-%E4%B8%80%E6%AC%BE%E5%BC%B7%E5%A4%A7%E7%9A%84-kotlin-mocking-library-part-3-4-79b40fb73964\">MockK 功能介紹：Relaxed Mocks, 再談 Verify, Capture</a></li>\n  <span class=\"nd\">@RelaxedMockK</span>\n<h3 id=\"injectmockks-dependency-order\">@InjectMockKs dependency order</h3>\nBy default, MockK processes them in reflection order; to resolve dependencies deterministically, enable dependency\n<span class=\"k\">fun</span> <span class=\"nf\">setUp</span><span class=\"p\">()</span> <span class=\"p\">=</span> <span class=\"nc\">MockKAnnotations</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">this</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">useDepend\nEnabling <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">useDependencyOrder</code> adds an approximate 3-5% performance overhead during initialization.</p>\n  <span class=\"nd\">@RelaxedMockK</span>\n  <span class=\"nd\">@RelaxedMockK</span>\n<p>Additionally, it adds the possibility to use <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">@MockK</code> and <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">@RelaxedMockK</code> on test function parameters:</p>\n<span class=\"k\">fun</span> <span class=\"nf\">calculateAddsValues1</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nd\">@MockK</span> <span class=\"n\">car1</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nc\">Car</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nd\">@RelaxedMockK</span> <span class=\"n\">car2</span><span\nthe <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">mockk.junit.extension.keepmocks=true</code> property.\nproperty to disable calling it in the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">@AfterAll</code> callback.\n<h4 id=\"declarative-enabling-of-dependency-order\">Declarative enabling of dependency order</h4>\n<p>You can enable topological dependency resolution of <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">@InjectMockKs</code> by also annotating your test class with <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">@MockKExtension.UseDependencyOrder</code>.</p>\n<p>This will internally process each test instance of the annotated class with <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">MockKAnnotations.init(useDependencyOrder==true)</code>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"relaxed-mock\">Relaxed mock</h3>\n<p>A <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">relaxed mock</code> is the mock that returns some simple value for all functions.\n<div class=\"language-kotlin highlighter-rouge\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre class=\"highlight\"><code><span class=\"kd\">val</span> <span class=\"py\">car</span> <span class=\"p\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mockk</span><span class=\"p\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nc\">Car</span><span class=\"p\">&gt;(</span><span clas\n<p>Note: relaxed mocking is working badly with generic return types. A class cast exception is usually thrown in this case.\n<div class=\"language-kotlin highlighter-rouge\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre class=\"highlight\"><code><span class=\"kd\">val</span> <span class=\"py\">func</span> <span class=\"p\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mockk</span><span class=\"p\">&lt;()</span> <span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"nc\">Car</span><span\n<span class=\"c1\">// this line is workaround, without it the relaxed mock would throw a class cast exception on the next line</span>\nThis is possible by passing <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">callOriginal()</code> to <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">answers</code>, which works for both relaxed and non-relaxed mocks.</p>\n<h3 id=\"mock-relaxed-for-functions-returning-unit\">Mock relaxed for functions returning Unit</h3>\n<p>If you want <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">Unit</code>-returning functions to be relaxed, you can use <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">relaxUnitFun = true</code> as an argument to the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">mockk</code> function,\n<span class=\"kd\">val</span> <span class=\"py\">car</span> <span class=\"p\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mockk</span><span class=\"p\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nc\">Car</span><span class=\"p\">&gt;(</span><span class=\"n\">relaxed</span> <span class=\"p\">=</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">val</span> <span class=\"py\">car</span> <span class=\"p\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mockk</span><span class=\"p\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nc\">Car</span><span class=\"p\">&gt;(</span><span class=\"n\">relaxed</span> <span class=\"p\">=</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<p>To mock coroutines you need to add another dependency to the support library.</p>\n<pre>testImplementation \"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core:x.x\"</pre>\n&lt;dependency&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;</pre>\n<code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">confirmVerified</code> accepts function/property references, but scoped confirmation works only for references backed by static mocks (typically top-level or module-wide extension references used with <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-roug\nIf you pass <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">clear = true</code> to <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">confirmVerified</code> with function/property references, only selected references are cleared.\n<span class=\"nf\">every</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">mock</span> <span class=\"n\">getProperty</span> <span class=\"s\">\"speed\"</span> <span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"n\">returns</span> <span class=\"mi\">33</span>\n<span class=\"nf\">every</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">mock</span> <span class=\"n\">setProperty</span> <span class=\"s\">\"acceleration\"</span> <span class=\"n\">value</span> <span class=\"nf\">less</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"\n<span class=\"nf\">verify</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">mock</span> <span class=\"n\">getProperty</span> <span class=\"s\">\"speed\"</span> <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"nf\">verify</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">mock</span> <span class=\"n\">setProperty</span> <span class=\"s\">\"acceleration\"</span> <span class=\"n\">value</span> <span class=\"nf\">less</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\n<h3 id=\"property-backing-fields\">Property backing fields</h3>\n<p>Note: in the examples below, we use <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">propertyType</code> to specify the type of the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">fieldValue</code>.\nUse <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">nullablePropertyType</code> to specify a nullable type.</p>\n<span class=\"nf\">every</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">mock</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">property</span> <span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"nf\">answers</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">fieldValue</span> <span class=\"p\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">6</s\n<span class=\"nf\">every</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">mock</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">property</span> <span class=\"p\">=</span> <span class=\"nf\">any</span><span class=\"p\">()</span> <span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"n\">propertyType</span> <span class=\"nc\">Int</s\n<span class=\"nf\">every</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">mock</span> <span class=\"n\">getProperty</span> <span class=\"s\">\"property\"</span> <span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"n\">propertyType</span> <span class=\"nc\">Int</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"k\">class</span> <span \n<span class=\"nf\">every</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">mock</span> <span class=\"n\">setProperty</span> <span class=\"s\">\"property\"</span> <span class=\"n\">value</span> <span class=\"n\">any</span><span class=\"p\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nc\">Int</span><span class=\"p\">&gt;()</span> <span cla\n    <span class=\"n\">mock</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">property</span> <span class=\"p\">=</span> <span class=\"nf\">any</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span> <span class=\"n\">propertyType</span> <span class=\"nc\">Int</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nf\">answers</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n  <li>Create the configuration file at <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">src/test/resources/mockk.properties</code>.</li>\n</span><span class=\"py\">relaxed</span><span class=\"p\">=</span><span class=\"s\">true|false</span>\n      <th><strong>Property</strong></th>\n      <td><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">relaxed</code></td>\n      <td>Enable relaxed mocking globally</td>\n      <td>Enable relaxed mocking for Unit-returning functions</td>\n<p>If both files exist, <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">mockk.properties</code> takes precedence. The legacy location is deprecated and will be removed in a future version.</p>\n      <td><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">propertyType Class</code></td>\n      <td><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">nullablePropertyType Class</code></td>\n      <td>accessor to the property backing field</td>\n      <td>accessor to the property backing field with <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">Any?</code> type</td>\n      <td>value being set, cast to the same type as the property backing field</td>\n<p>You can configure Restricted Mocking behavior using the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">mockk.properties</code> configuration file described in the <a href=\"#configuration-file\">Configuration File</a> section.</p>\n    systemProperty(\"mockk.throwExceptionOnBadMock\", \"true\")\n<p>You can also do a variable system property and pass the value\n    systemProperty(\"mockk.throwExceptionOnBadMock\", System.getProperty(\"mockk.throwExceptionOnBadMock\"))\n<p>You can add the property to your <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">gradle.properties</code> file:</p>\nin your <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">build.gradle</code> will override the value that is set in <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">mockk.properties</code> file.</p>\n<p>You can restrict <strong>custom classes</strong> from being mocked using the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">mockk.properties</code> configuration file.\n<p>Add the following to your <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">mockk.properties</code> file:</p>\n            if (!ga.hasOwnProperty(\"loaded\") || ga.loaded != true || (event.which != 1 && event.which != 2)) {\nlen 225227\nURL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mockk/mockk/1.14.9/README.md\nAll you need to get started is just to add a dependency to `MockK` library.\n#### Gradle/Maven dependency\ntestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk:${mockkVersion}\"\n  <pre>testImplementation(\"io.mockk:mockk:${mockkVersion}\")</pre>\n &lt;dependency&gt;\n &lt;/dependency&gt;\ntestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-android:${mockkVersion}\"\ntestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-agent:${mockkVersion}\"\nandroidTestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-android:${mockkVersion}\"\nandroidTestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-agent:${mockkVersion}\"\ntestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk:${mockkVersion}\"\ntestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-bdd:${mockkVersion}\"\nandroidTestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-android:${mockkVersion}\"\nandroidTestImplementation \"io.mockk:mockk-bdd-android:${mockkVersion}\"\n - [MockK 功能介紹：Relaxed Mocks, 再談 Verify, Capture](https://medium.com/joe-tsai/mockk-%E4%B8%80%E6%AC%BE%E5%BC%B7%E5%A4%A7%E7%9A%84-kotlin-mocking-library-part-3-4-79b40fb73964)\n  @RelaxedMockK\n### @InjectMockKs dependency order\nBy default, MockK processes them in reflection order; to resolve dependencies deterministically, enable dependency\nfun setUp() = MockKAnnotations.init(this, useDependencyOrder = true)\nEnabling `useDependencyOrder` adds an approximate 3-5% performance overhead during initialization.\n  @RelaxedMockK\n  @RelaxedMockK\nAdditionally, it adds the possibility to use `@MockK` and `@RelaxedMockK` on test function parameters:\nfun calculateAddsValues1(@MockK car1: Car, @RelaxedMockK car2: Car) {\nthe `mockk.junit.extension.keepmocks=true` property.\nproperty to disable calling it in the `@AfterAll` callback.\n### Relaxed mock\nA `relaxed mock` is the mock that returns some simple value for all functions.\nval car = mockk<Car>(relaxed = true)\nNote: relaxed mocking is working badly with generic return types. A class cast exception is usually thrown in this case.\nval func = mockk<() -> Car>(relaxed = true) // in this case invoke function has generic return type\n// this line is workaround, without it the relaxed mock would throw a class cast exception on the next line\nThis is possible by passing `callOriginal()` to `answers`, which works for both relaxed and non-relaxed mocks.\n### Mock relaxed for functions returning Unit\nIf you want `Unit`-returning functions to be relaxed, you can use `relaxUnitFun = true` as an argument to the `mockk` function,\nval car = mockk<Car>(relaxed = true)\nval car = mockk<Car>(relaxed = true)\nTo mock coroutines you need to add another dependency to the support library.\n<pre>testImplementation \"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core:x.x\"</pre>\n&lt;dependency&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;</pre>\nevery { mock getProperty \"speed\" } returns 33\nevery { mock setProperty \"acceleration\" value less(5) } just runs\nverify { mock getProperty \"speed\" }\nverify { mock setProperty \"acceleration\" value less(5) }\n### Property backing fields\nNote: in the examples below, we use `propertyType` to specify the type of the `fieldValue`.\nUse `nullablePropertyType` to specify a nullable type.\nevery { mock.property } answers { fieldValue + 6 }\nevery { mock.property = any() } propertyType Int::class answers { fieldValue += value }\nevery { mock getProperty \"property\" } propertyType Int::class answers { fieldValue + 6 }\nevery { mock setProperty \"property\" value any<Int>() } propertyType Int::class answers  { fieldValue += value }\n    mock.property = any()\n} propertyType Int::class answers {\n1. Create the configuration file at `src/test/resources/mockk.properties`.\nrelaxed=true|false\n| **Property**                    | **Description**                                                                                 | **Default Value** |\n| `relaxed`                       | Enable relaxed mocking globally                                                                 | `false`           |\n| `relaxUnitFun`                  | Enable relaxed mocking for Unit-returning functions                                             | `false`           |\nIf both files exist, `mockk.properties` takes precedence. The legacy location is deprecated and will be removed in a future version.\n| `propertyType Class`         | specify the type of the backing field accessor                                                                     |\n| `nullablePropertyType Class` | specify the type of the backing field accessor as a nullable type                                                  |\n| `fieldValue`                  | accessor to the property backing field                                  |\n| `fieldValueAny`               | accessor to the property backing field with `Any?` type                 |\n| `value`                       | value being set, cast to the same type as the property backing field    |\nYou can configure Restricted Mocking behavior using the `mockk.properties` configuration file described in the [Configuration File](#configuration-file) section.\n    systemProperty(\"mockk.throwExceptionOnBadMock\", \"true\")\nYou can also do a variable system property and pass the value\n    systemProperty(\"mockk.throwExceptionOnBadMock\", System.getProperty(\"mockk.throwExceptionOnBadMock\"))\nYou can add the property to your `gradle.properties` file:\nin your `build.gradle` will override the value that is set in `mockk.properties` file.\nYou can restrict **custom classes** from being mocked using the `mockk.properties` configuration file.\nAdd the following to your `mockk.properties` file:\nlen 73904\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782351998664}]}
